<TITLE> Further police remands in Gautam murder case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 29 (bdnews24.com)  A Dhaka court on Tuesday granted police four days to question Zakir Hossain alias Kaillya Zakir and Abdur Rauf Bhuiyan in relation to the killing of sub inspector Gautam killing. Dhaka Metropolitan Magistrate Mostafa Shahriar Khan granted the remand following a police request for ten days remand. The police said that they needed to take the men into custody to find out the weapon used in the killing and the motives behind the murder. Another man, also called Zakir Hossain has also been arrested and taken into police remand on Tuesday for four days The judge said that the Zakir Hossain whose alias was Kaillya Zakir was the actual killer of sub-inspector Gautam, not the Zakir who had been remanded earlier. No bail petition was filed with the court on behalf of Kaillya Zakir. Goutam Roy, a police sub-inspector of Banglsal Police Station, was shot dead at old Dhaka's Dholaikhal road on Apr 20. Law enforcement agencies received information that a Zakir and a Haider had direct involvement with the murder. Since then police and RAB have arrested two Zakirs and two Haiders who are still to be correctly identified. bd
